The paper discusses pricing strategies in crowdsourcing systems, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also considers the computational tractability of the pricing schemes, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the notion of privacy concerns in personalized pricing, which relates to cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY). Finally, the paper validates its findings through simulations and experiments, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
